21/05/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The opposition party Union of Democratic Forces (UDF) said on Tuesday (20 May) it would submit a no confidence motion against Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg on Friday, with the vote expected by month's end. Nadezhda Mihailova, leader of the right-wing party, cited the failure of the government's domestic policies. UDF holds 51 of the 240 seats in parliament. (Standart, Trud, 24 Chassa - 21/05/03; BTA - 20/05/03)
